Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{1}(chopped into 2cm chunks) into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Halve the @lime{1}(halved and cut into wedges) and cut into wedges. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%carton}.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal pan and transfer to an ovenproof dish before baking.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, wide-bottomed #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

Add the @yellow Thai style paste{45%g} and fry until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @coconut milk{180%ml}, @soy sauce{25%ml}, @peanut butter{30%g}, @sugar{1%tsp} and @water for the sauce{150%ml}. Mix well until combined.

Bring the sauce back up to the boil, then stir through the @diced British chicken breast{240%g}, sweet potato chunks and chickpeas.

Pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the chicken is cooked through and the sauce has thickened, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

== Jasmine Rice ==

When there is 20 mins left of cooking time left, pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting lid.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Finish ==

When the curry has finished cooking, add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Squeeze in some lime from a lime wedge. Taste and season with more @salt{}, @pepper or @lime juice{} if you feel it needs it.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and share between your #bowls{}.

Top with the chicken and sweet potato curry and sprinkle over the @salted peanuts{25%g} to finish.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges alongside for squeezing over.

Enjoy!